Because my schedule is busy, I cannot check every post, so I rely on a few trusted friends to warn me about rumors that spread in our community. This social support network, though small, provides a reality check that counters the echo chambers of algorithms. I also set limits on my screen time—just a couple of hours each week—so I can stay grounded and avoid the anxiety that comes from endless scrolling. When I do encounter misinformation, I choose to respond calmly, not with anger but with facts, because I know that shouting only fuels the cycle.

